Lagos State House of Assembly on Tuesday confirmed Sikiru Adeniji Salami, nominated by Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu, as the substantive Auditor-General. The Speaker, Mudashiru Obasa announced the confirmation following a voice vote by lawmakers during plenary. The University of Lagos (UNILAG) and Federal University of Technology Akure (FUTA) alumni earlier appeared for screening. Salami, 57, is a member, Chartered Accountants of Nigeria (ICAN), Chartered Institute of Taxation of Nigeria (CITN) and Institute of Certified Public Accountants of Nigeria. The Fellow Chartered Accountant (FCA) is also a member of the Associate of Chartered Taxation Institute (ACTI), Certified Public Accountant (CPA), and International Academy of Forensics (IAF). However, the Lagos State Anti-Corruption and Transparency Commission (amendment) bill 2022 scaled second reading. During the debate, Gbolahan Yishawu (Eti-Osa 2) and Victor Akande commended their colleagues for acting responsively and responsibly. The House Committee on Judiciary is expected to present its report next week.